Three children aged 10 months, two and four years, died in a house fire while their parents were away on Tuesday morning.The incident took place at about 7am at Makawani village in Chuka Igambang ombe constituency, Tharaka Nithi county.Kithangani sublocation assistant chief Jamleck Mugambi said the children's parents locked them inside the house when they left for their farm.Margaret Muthoni, a neighbour, said she heard screams as she was heading to work. I rushed to the scene and found neighbours trying to help but the fire had consumed half the house," she said.Mugambi said neighbours tried in vain to put out the fire. He said police later took the bodies to Chuka hospital mortuary.The cause of the fire was not clear but the assistant chief said it may have been the solar system the family had been using.